we doing, Chefs?

01:01.548 --> 01:02.484
-Bad.
-Not good.

01:02.517 --> 01:03.919
Cool. Good.

01:04.588 --> 01:07.092
-When are you gonna see him?
-Um, tonight.

01:07.527 --> 01:08.429
My Mom's birthday dinner.

01:08.462 --> 01:10.633
-That'll be nice.
-SYDNEY: Yeah, super.

01:10.666 --> 01:12.637
Are we still good
to jam on menu later?

01:12.670 --> 01:14.073
-CARMY: Yes, Chef.
-SYDNEY: Okay.

01:14.106 --> 01:15.342
-Yo, Carm, fridge guy.
-Yo.

01:17.212 --> 01:18.249
I'll call him back.

01:18.282 --> 01:19.418
My bad.

01:19.451 --> 01:20.553
-Yo.
-CARMY: Yo.

01:20.586 --> 01:21.589
-Toilet's still fucked.
-SUGAR: I'm aware.

01:21.622 --> 01:22.524
I'm trading with the guy.

01:22.557 --> 01:24.026
No go on the door-pull.

01:24.059 --> 01:25.463
That's a really crucial part.

01:25.496 --> 01:27.099
-They are 5K.
-CARMY: Yeah.

01:27.132 --> 01:28.536
They're hand cast in Italy.

01:28.569 --> 01:30.507
Yeah, and we're in Illinois.

01:30.540 --> 01:32.377
Ugh, what about the Danish teak?

01:32.410 --> 01:34.515
Hmm. Those are 3K,
which you said cost 2K.

01:34.548 --> 01:35.550
The bronze brutalist?

01:35.583 --> 01:36.619
Those are actually 2K.

01:36.652 --> 01:38.155
You can have
the Naperville Nickel.

01:38.188 --> 01:39.391
Are you feeling okay, Nat?

01:39.424 --> 01:40.960
By the way,
you look a little pale.

01:40.993 --> 01:42.163
Is it the Naperville Nickel?

01:42.196 --> 01:44.033
I'm fine. Just, uh...

01:44.066 --> 01:46.472
Sometimes
I look like February.

01:46.505 --> 01:47.507
Sure.

01:47.540 --> 01:48.475
-Also, Carm...
-CARMY: Yeah.

01:48.509 --> 01:50.613
SUGAR:
Your fork numbers,
not fantastic.

01:50.646 --> 01:51.682
