02:06.244 --> 02:08.282
my sister doesn't think
I'm a genius, so...

02:10.085 --> 02:11.322
It doesn't hurt.

02:11.355 --> 02:12.958
...have your sandpaper
attached to your pole.

02:12.991 --> 02:15.463
Make a few passes
up and down like this.

02:15.496 --> 02:16.498
How long is this video?

02:16.899 --> 02:19.137
MAN (over phone):
And you wanna make sure
to spend extra time...

02:19.170 --> 02:19.838
Stop.

02:19.872 --> 02:22.042
MAN:
...any uneven spots.

02:22.075 --> 02:23.513
Alright.

02:23.546 --> 02:24.648
Alright, gentlemen.

02:24.681 --> 02:26.151
I'm taking over this operation.

02:26.184 --> 02:28.121
Now before we can
execute a deep clean,

02:28.154 --> 02:29.090
we gotta peel all this paint.

02:29.123 --> 02:30.092
That's what I just said.

02:30.125 --> 02:31.529
Yeah, but what you didn't say,

02:31.562 --> 02:33.131
what you didn't say
is that there's no reason

02:33.164 --> 02:35.336
to move these lockers twice.

02:35.369 --> 02:36.505
Marcus, we got putty?

02:36.538 --> 02:38.008
We have to move everything out

02:38.041 --> 02:39.076
before we scrape.

02:39.109 --> 02:40.246
Richie, you're not listening.

02:40.279 --> 02:41.047
Look, I don't
wanna choose sides,

02:41.080 --> 02:42.216
but it seems
like moving the lockers

02:42.250 --> 02:43.419
is the best way to do this.

02:43.452 --> 02:45.256
Wow, Marcus, I never
thought I'd see the day

02:45.289 --> 02:47.460
where you would form
an actual alliance
with Neil Geoff.

02:47.493 --> 02:49.598
Alright, Richie,
it's not an alliance.
It's just like common sense--

02:49.631 --> 02:50.733
It sure sounded
like an alliance.

02:50.766 --> 02:51.702
No, no. It's just like
common sense.

02:51.735 --> 02:52.570
Move the lockers first.

02:52.604 --> 02:54.975
I'm watching a guy
who does this shit

02:55.008 --> 02:56.412
all the fuckin' time.

02:56.445 --> 02:57.447
He just tarps over.

02:57.480 --> 02:59.451
I'm trying to save you lizards
some moves here.

02:59.484 --> 03:01.522
I'll tell you what,
you take half the guys
in the dining room--

03:01.555 --> 03:03.058
-There's only three guys.
-Dude, I need

03:03.091 --> 03:04.595
all the hands to move
the lockers out right now.

03:04.628 --> 03:06.332
Okay, fine.
We'll do it your way.

03:06.365 --> 03:08.001
You take, uh, two guys--

03:08.034 --> 03:09.271
-It's still your fuckin' way.
-RICHIE: Good? Go.

03:09.304 --> 03:10.473
No, it's not my fuckin' way.

03:10.506 --> 03:11.742
There's not sides!

03:11.775 --> 03:14.013
There's one way,
it's the fuckin' right way!

03:14.046 --> 03:15.114
Watch this.

03:15.583 --> 03:18.154
-Nat?
-You just, you called Mom?

03:18.187 --> 03:19.691
-You called Mom?
-Yes, honey.

03:19.724 --> 03:22.129
Okay, listen, so...

03:22.162 --> 03:24.233
Okay, I just wanna do it right.

03:24.267 --> 03:26.170
And I do think that we need
to move the lockers out first

03:26.203 --> 03:27.105
before we scrape.

03:27.138 --> 03:29.210
So then move
the lockers first, my love.

03:29.244 --> 03:30.413
Then we're just gonna
move them right back

03:30.446 --> 03:31.715
where they are, Natalie.

03:31.748 --> 03:33.218
Why fuck 'em up?

03:33.252 --> 03:35.188
Don't start bossing
people around, please.

03:35.723 --> 03:37.794
Natalie, I'm trying
to head up this operation.

03:37.827 --> 03:39.731
I'm trying to
assert myself, okay?

03:39.764 --> 03:42.437
I don't know what they teach you
about leadership at the bank,

03:42.470 --> 03:45.643
but in this kind of a situation,
what you need is an alpha,

03:45.676 --> 03:47.012
and that is not Fak.

03:47.045 --> 03:48.282
They can smell his pheromones.

03:48.315 --> 03:50.219
They are weak as shit.
That's just chemistry.

03:50.253 --> 03:52.088
Move the fucking lockers.

03:53.459 --> 03:54.695
-Are you alright?
-SUGAR: I'm fine.

03:54.728 --> 03:55.597
You want a Sprite?

03:55.630 --> 03:58.034
-You look kinda green.
-SUGAR: Mm-mmm.

04:00.406 --> 04:02.477
For real, you're shitty.

04:02.510 --> 04:03.779
-I didn't wanna do it wrong.
-You're shitty.

04:03.812 --> 04:04.715
I didn't wanna do it wrong.

04:04.748 --> 04:06.050
You did call Mom, though.

04:06.083 --> 04:06.785
Thank you, Marcus.

04:06.818 --> 04:08.121
Yeah, but you were wrong.

04:08.154 --> 04:09.457
What? You were.

04:12.397 --> 04:13.665
(quietly) Move 'em.

04:14.199 --> 04:17.039
Okay, Chefs, we are
three months out from open

04:17.072 --> 04:19.210
and I want everybody
to stay sharp.

04:19.244 --> 04:22.350
So we're gonna be sending
you guys to culinary school.

04:24.788 --> 04:26.325
But I already know
how to do it.

04:26.358 --> 04:28.228
Oh, well,
it's not about that, Chef.

04:28.262 --> 04:30.132
It's about, you know,
repetition, right?

04:30.165 --> 04:32.069
And it's already
built into the budget,

04:32.102 --> 04:33.239
so you'll still be paid hourly.

04:33.272 --> 04:35.142
Oh, I'm in.

04:35.175 --> 04:37.078
Let's do it, baby!

04:38.549 --> 04:40.853
Uh, Ebra, this is gonna be
a really great way

04:40.886 --> 04:43.057
to take advantage
of our time here.

04:44.828 --> 04:46.332
I don't want
to wear a uniform.

04:46.365 --> 04:48.736
Okay. Well, you can
discuss that with the school.

04:48.769 --> 04:50.472
It's not that kinda uniform.

04:50.806 --> 04:52.276
SYDNEY: This is exciting.

04:53.312 --> 04:54.514
I accept.

04:54.547 --> 04:55.850
Great. Okay. Yeah.

04:55.883 --> 04:57.186
When do we start?

04:57.219 --> 04:58.755
-(indistinct yelling)
-(loud thud)

05:03.197 --> 05:04.501
-RICHIE: Go left.
-FAK: I'm going left!

05:04.534 --> 05:05.536
You gotta go right.

05:05.569 --> 05:07.507
No, it's-it's the fridge handle.

05:07.540 --> 05:09.210
The fridge handle,
it keeps, um...

05:09.244 --> 05:11.415
It's breaking.
Yeah, it's breaking off, yeah.

05:11.448 --> 05:12.617
-FAK: Okay!
-Not left.

05:12.650 --> 05:14.388
-FAK: Pick it up!
-Come on.

05:14.421 --> 05:17.159
-My number is 7-7-3...
-RICHIE: What are you doing?

05:17.192 --> 05:19.096
-...5-5-5...
-(object clatters)

05:19.731 --> 05:23.305
...uh, 0... 0-9-0-1.

05:23.338 --> 05:25.777
-RICHIE: Left.
-You gotta pick it,
pick it up, too!

05:25.810 --> 05:27.781
-Why are you
fighting me on this?
-FAK: I'm not!

05:27.814 --> 05:29.150
CARMY:
Yo! Yo! Guys, guys.

05:29.183 --> 05:32.424
I think I know the answer,
but can you please
shut the fuck up.

05:32.457 --> 05:34.728
-RICHIE: Yo. Cousin.
-FAK: Carmy, I wanted
to do it the right way--

05:34.761 --> 05:36.865
I had this shit all dialed
and then this cucumber,

05:36.898 --> 05:38.736
-he's gotta tell Mom--
-...and he made it his.

05:38.769 --> 05:40.640
I can't get a grip
on the lockers 'cause
Mikey's is still locked.

05:40.673 --> 05:43.211
Alright. Hey. Got it.
Thank you. Thank you.

05:43.245 --> 05:44.514
Marcus agrees with me.

05:44.547 --> 05:46.150
(Richie scoffs)

05:51.395 --> 05:53.197
FAK:
It's-- it's still here.

05:55.603 --> 05:57.707
Just fuckin' open it.

05:57.740 --> 05:58.876
FAK: Okay, hold on.

05:58.909 --> 05:59.877
Okay.

06:02.417 --> 06:03.518
There, Bear.

06:03.852 --> 06:05.423
SUGAR: What's goin' on?

06:05.456 --> 06:06.558
We gotta cut it.

06:07.293 --> 06:08.328
Oh.

06:11.635 --> 06:12.570
(whirring)

06:17.346 --> 06:18.516
(lock thuds)

06:18.549 --> 06:20.285
(whirring stops)

06:42.797 --> 06:44.467
June 5th, 2010.

06:46.237 --> 06:47.606
Taste of Chicago.

06:48.207 --> 06:49.911
-The booth.
-The booth. (chuckles)

06:52.817 --> 06:54.219
That was really fun.

06:59.764 --> 07:00.899
Here you go.

07:04.340 --> 07:05.977
Yo, you wanna work
at the apartment?

07:06.010 --> 07:07.347
-SUGAR: Yeah.
-Yeah?

07:07.380 --> 07:08.883
-Yo, Chef.
-SYDNEY: Hmm?

07:08.916 --> 07:11.655
-I need more, um, inspiration.
-What do you mean?

07:11.688 --> 07:12.957
I went through
all those books you gave me.

07:12.990 --> 07:15.696
-All the cookbooks?
-All of 'em.

07:15.729 --> 07:17.700
Okay, yeah,
I'll-I'll think on it.

07:17.733 --> 07:19.438
-Cool.
-Cool.

07:19.471 --> 07:20.539
Um...

07:21.842 --> 07:23.745
-Was that...
-Mikey's locker.

07:24.213 --> 07:25.783
-SYDNEY: Hmm.
-Yeah.

07:28.322 --> 07:29.590
There was just a hat in it?

07:30.993 --> 07:32.663
-Syd.
-What?

07:33.799 --> 07:35.470
Come on. Asshole.

07:35.503 --> 07:37.773
What? I'm not an asshole.

07:38.876 --> 07:40.480
Hey, I'm not an asshole.

07:40.513 --> 07:42.584
