felt like a sort of panic

09:46.464 --> 09:47.934
'cause I knew
I just had to keep 'em.

09:47.967 --> 09:48.969
I had to retain 'em.

09:49.002 --> 09:50.037
Um...

09:50.772 --> 09:52.844
And your brain
does this weird thing

09:52.877 --> 09:56.818
where it just bypasses
any sense of joy.

09:56.851 --> 09:59.590
It just like
attaches itself to dread.

10:00.058 --> 10:02.062
And, um, I don't know,
after those ten seconds,

10:02.095 --> 10:03.632
I had to turn over
a really slow table

10:03.665 --> 10:04.834
'cause the, uh,

10:04.867 --> 10:06.538
entire United Nations
Security Council

10:06.571 --> 10:07.640
was coming in.

10:10.579 --> 10:12.449
So, normal. Totally normal.

10:13.485 --> 10:14.520
Yeah.

10:24.641 --> 10:26.812
Fak? Fak?

10:26.845 --> 10:28.181
What's this brown shit?

10:28.214 --> 10:29.818
MARCUS:
I've seen some of those, too.

10:29.851 --> 10:31.655
Also, why was there
a hockey stick
behind the locker?

10:31.688 --> 10:33.626
-Sworn to secrecy.
-Yo, can we switch?

10:33.659 --> 10:34.861
You can see fine
from right there.

10:34.894 --> 10:35.829
